    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p> <p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Add the <strong>spelt</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat</p> <p>Cook for 15-20 min or until cooked through but with a slight bite</p> <p>Once cooked, drain and rinse under cold water until cool</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chicken-courgette-and-chilli-mint-spelt-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, zest the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into a bowl</p> <p>Place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces</p> <p>Add the<strong> sliced chicken</strong> to the bowl of<strong> lemon zest</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p> <p>Give everything a good old mix up</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chicken-courgette-and-chilli-mint-spelt-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken</strong> with any&nbsp;remaining marinade to a baking tray&nbsp;</p> <p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until cooked through</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chicken-courgette-and-chilli-mint-spelt-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top and tail the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Peel lengths of <strong>courgette</strong> until you end up with a pile of courgette 'ribbons'</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chicken-courgette-and-chilli-mint-spelt-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p> <p>Cut the<strong>&nbsp;red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop \ufb01nely</p> <p>Strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> and chop them finely, discarding the stems&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chicken-courgette-and-chilli-mint-spelt-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with the juice of the<strong> lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and 1 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p> <p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and half the <strong>mint leaves</strong> (save the rest for later!) &ndash; this is your <strong>lemony dressing</strong>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chicken-courgette-and-chilli-mint-spelt-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Gently wash and pat the <strong>lamb's lettuce</strong> dry</p> <p>Add the <strong>lamb's l</strong><strong>ettuce</strong>,<strong> courgette ribbons</strong>, <strong>cooked spelt</strong> and<strong> remaining mint leaves</strong> to a very large mixing bowl</p> <p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, pour over the <strong>lemony dressing</strong> and give everything a good old mix up</p> <p>Remove the <strong>cooked chicken</strong> from the oven and slice it finely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chicken-courgette-and-chilli-mint-spelt-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> courgette, chilli &amp; mint salad</strong> topped with the<strong> sliced chicken</strong></p> <p>Garnish with the <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
